Haitian men generally expect their partners to accept various degrees of infidelity.

One study of working women in Haiti revealed that many women were intensely dependent on their partners, citing themselves as “insignificant” and feeling that their spouses own their lives and bodies. Their abusive partners often take away their Social Security cards, passports, driver’s licences, and other personal documents, which they use to effectively trap them in the relationship.

One study, which reported that 97% of women in Haiti reported being victims of some form of violence, especially sexual violence, despite fear of bringing the stigma of divorce upon their families.
